d weapon last round hasn’t elapsed, your second weapon will not swing, even if you succeed your dual-wield check.  See where I’m going with this?  No?  Then trust me that you want your lower delay weapon in your off hand.  This is hugely counter-intuitive, so either work through the logic or just trust me and do it.&quot;<br><br>This came from a Tunare guild's webpage, <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.orderofconcord.com/warrior_guide.htm">www.orderofconcord.com/warrior_guide.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>The author is right, this does seem extremely counter-intuitive, if not flat wrong. To me, the low delay weapon should go in the primary, as the secondary strike can only come after a primary strike.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxorizjebekis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xoriz Jebekis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.go56.com/images/icon.png" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 9:35:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.go56.com/images/x.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Should the lowest delay weapon be primary in a dualwield</span><hr size=1> Neither hand relies on the other hand. &lt;- period <p><p align="center"><map name="FPMap0"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10201" shape="rect" coords="9, 3, 289, 52"><area href="http://altruisticvalorians.tripod.com" shape="rect" coords="102, 54, 202, 72"></map><img border="0" src="http://www.go56.com/images/xor.png" usemap="#FPMap0" width="302" height="77"></p></p><i