ary, adn a sword in secondary, hit attack, and nothign happened. Leads me to believe that u have to have a weapon and successfully attack to do a duel wield in primary.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Did you have something targetted other than yourself?  Because everytime I have put a lantern in my primary hand, my off hand still fires. <p><Table Style='Filter: Alpha(Opacity=100, FinishOpacity=50, Style=3, StartX=85, FinishX=20, StartY=0, FinishY=0)'><B><Font Color=White Face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741" target="magelo"><Font Color=White>Turom Toesmasher</Font></a><br>57 Myrmidon<br>The Seventh Hammer<br></Font></B></Table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uswanda08.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swanda08</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/25/02 9:38:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Should the lowest delay weapon be primary in a dualwield</span><hr size=1> better ratio instead of speed in offhand since no damage bonus applies<br><br>1 hit more in a minute will not generate thta much more agro anyways <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uygnirthundersson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ygnir Thundersson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF000