icProfile?language=EN>smushums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 620<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/02 6:11:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Should the lowest delay weapon be primary in a dualwield</span><hr size=1> heres a duel wield question i never really thought about.<br><br>do you have to 'land' both of your duel wield hits to attempt a triple?<br><br>i got self hits off so i dont really have a clue <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udahnlor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dahnlor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/02 10:36:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mortgage411.com/clients/276753/member-dw.jpg width=112 height=115></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Should the lowest delay weapon be primary in a dualwield</span><hr size=1> Triple attack (which only occurs at level 60) only happens with the primary hand, and the attacks do not need to connect.  The secondary weapon has its own double attack check whenever the dual wield skill check is successful and is not affected by the primary hand at all.<br><br><br>It appears a couple of posts above missed the log I posted above.  Perhaps it requires a little more explanation.  To recap the weapons used, the primary weapon is a piercer with 39 delay, and the secondary weapon is a slasher with 19 delay.  If the secondary weapon has to wait for the primary to recycle, you would only ever see both weapons attacking at the same time.<br><br>The log begins with a piercing attack (primary weapon):<br><br>[Mon Feb 11 14:53:24 2002] You pierce A Stonegrabber for 48 points of damage. <br><br>Then, time-stamped one second later, I slash (secondary weapon):<br><br>[Mon Feb 11 14:53:25 2002] You slash A Stonegrabber for 15 points of damage. <br>[Mon Feb 11 14:53:25 2002] You slash A Stonegrabber for 33 points of damage. <br><br>One second after that, there is another slash (a second successful dual wield attack, primary hand has not yet recycled):<br><br>[Mon Feb 11 14:53:26 2002] You try to slash A Stonegrabber, but miss! <br>[Mon Feb 11 14:53:26 2002] You slash A Stonegrabber for 14 points of damage. <br><br>And finally, time-stamped one second after the second offhand attack, the primary weapon's delay finally recycles and we have a pierce:<br><br>[Mon Feb 11 14:53:27 2002] You pierce A Stonegrabber for 25 points of damage. <br>[Mon Feb 11 14:53:27 2002] You pierce A Stonegrabber for 25 points of damage.<br><br>Misses were turned on, so there clearly was not a primary weapon attack between the secondary attacks.  If the secondary hand needs to wait for the primary hand delay to refresh in order to attack again, the above would have been impossible. <p>Dahnlor Wiffingblade<BR>Level 60 Half Elf Warlord<BR>The Kindred - Drinal<BR><I>...and they cowered in fear for what had so nearly come to pass!</I><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubumwuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bumwuk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.citizenl.com/Triumphicon2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Sup